    Layout = null;
}

<h1 class="heading">Improvement Activities</h1>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <p>
                This performance category is weighted at 15% toward your final score. for full participation in the improvement activities performance category,
                clinicians can engage in up to four (medium-weighted) activities, rather than the proposed six (medium-weighted) ativities,
            </p>
            <p>
                This report category is compiled of three scoring sections totaling to 155 overall points
                that will be capped at 100 possible unweighted category points.
            </p>
            <p>
                The base score section is comprised of the required measures and objects. To obtion the
                required 50 base points, you must attest to the Security and Risk Analysis measure and provide
                at least a 1 in the numerator for the numerator/denominator of the remaining measures.
            </p>
            <p>
                The submitted numerator and denominators of both the required and optional measure, except
                the e-prescribing measure, are included in the performance score section of 90 points. Along with
                the points based upon the rates of the measures, 10 of these points are provided by attesting
                yes to the immunization registry reporting. The patient Access and Health information Exchange
                required measures are worth double the points when using the 2014 CEHRT Edition than with the
                2015 CEHRT edition to compensate for the different in number of measure available.
            </p>
            <p>
                CEHRT bonus points are available based upon your answers provided on the improvement activities tab.
                Some activities have two check boxes, one to attest to engagement and another to attest to using CEHRT
                for this engagement. If at least one activity that is selected has both boxes checked, then you will obtaion
                10 Points.
            </p>
            <p>An additional 5 bonus points are available if you can attest "Yes" to the second button.</p>
        </div>


        <div class="col-md-8">
            <div class="vl" style="border-left: 1px solid black;">
                <h4 class="lines">Expanded Practice Access</h4>
                <table class="table table-bordered table-responsive table-hover">
                    <tr>Weighting</tr>
                    <tr>Activity</tr>
                    <tr>Engaged</tr>
                </table>


            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
